<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="ferror" id="ferror">ferror</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdio&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> <span class="kw3">ferror</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">FILE</span> <span class="sy2">*</span>stream <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
Checks the given stream for errors. In case of an error, use
perror() to determine which error has occured.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "ferror" [1-205] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit2"><a name="parameters" id="parameters">Parameters</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

<code>stream</code> - the file stream to be checked
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Parameters" [206-269] -->
<h3 class="sectionedit3"><a name="return_value" id="return_value">Return value</a></h3>
<div class="level3">

<p>

nonzero if errors have occurred, 0 otherwise
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT3 SECTION "Return value" [270-337] -->
